Package de.oth.blocklib.threading

Interface BlocklibExecutorService

All Superinterfaces:
java.util.concurrent.Executor, java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService, java.util.concurrent.ScheduledExecutorService
All Known Implementing Classes:
BlocklibExecutor
public interface BlocklibExecutorService
extends java.util.concurrent.ScheduledExecutorService
The interface Blocklib executor service. The main interface for job execution in the blocklib. All classes that use jobs should reference this interface.
Author:
Loher Florian
See Also:
ScheduledExecutorService, BlocklibExecutor

    • schedule

      <V> ScheduledCompletableFuture<V> schedule​(java.lang.Runnable command, V result, long delay, java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit unit)
      Submits a one-shot task that becomes enabled after the given delay.
      Parameters:
      command - the task to execute
      result - the predefined value that is returned upon completion of the task
      delay - the time from now to delay execution
      unit - the time unit of the delay parameter
      Returns:
      a ScheduledFuture representing pending completion of the task and whose get() method will return result upon completion
      Throws:
      java.util.concurrent.RejectedExecutionException - if the task cannot be scheduled for execution
      java.lang.NullPointerException - if command or unit is null

      <V> ScheduledCompletableFuture<V> schedule​(java.util.concurrent.Callable<V> callable, long delay, java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit unit, TaskPriority priority)

    • submit

      <V> java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture<V> submit​(java.util.concurrent.Callable<V> task, TaskPriority priority)
      Submits a value-returning task for execution that is executed after all tasks with a higher priority are finished and returns a Future representing the pending results of the task. The Future's get method will return the task's result upon successful completion.
      Parameters:
      priority - the priority
      Returns:
      a scheduled completable future representing pending completion that can be used to chain other jobs.
      See Also:
      submit(Callable)

      Parameters:

      Returns:

      See Also:
      BlocklibExecutorService#submit(Runnable, V)

    • submit

      java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture<java.lang.Void> submit​(java.lang.Runnable task, TaskPriority priority)
      Submits a Void-returning task for execution that is executed after all tasks with a higher priority are finished and returns a Future representing the pending execution of the task. The Future's get method will return null upon successful completion.
      Parameters:
      priority - the priority
      Returns:
      a completable future representing pending completion that can be used to chain other jobs.
      See Also:
      submit(Runnable)
